        "timestamp": "2019-04-17 19:26:34.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2\n\nI know I've seen other binary files committed recently but this is a bad idea. From what I've read it makes our git repository permanently grow by the size of the file, unless a painstaking process is taken to remove it later. \n\nFrom ONAP Commit Messages page: \"NEVER embed binary files including jar, war, tar, gz, gzip, zip in Gerrit\"\n\nhttps://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Commit+Messages \n\nSee this https://robinwinslow.uk/2013/06/11/dont-ever-commit-binary-files-to-git/ \nand https://www.perforce.com/blog/storing-large-binary-files-in-git-repositories\n\nWe should discuss as a team what we think should be allowed in the git repo, but I'd vote for code, text etc only. \n\nDo any of us want to sit around waiting for a long time to clone SO code?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
